snippet.textDisplay:
i feel so bad that NO one is talking abt my man Namjoon, but at the same time bighit really let him down with this. there is nothing to talk about in the first place. his rap part is too short, he is not in the front in any of the dance breaks, the camera in on him for like 30 seconds and he literally has no chance to shine, except of the "look at my feet down" moment. aint that awesome?

edit: and may i add, he is the only one with no new solo song. yes, persona is on the album, so that can count as a solo, but there is nothing new to talk about, which is kinda sad? why did bighit chose to let him have his moment in a small album with like six songs in total? even his outfits are lacking. now i hate to be the grumpy stan that complains about little stupid unimportant things, but i just wanted to mention how weird it seems to me that in an era in which everyone is stunningly amazing, RM is like... okay.

edit: and may i add, he is the only one with no *new* solo song. yes, persona is on the album, so that can count as a solo, but there is nothing new to talk about, which is kinda sad? why did bighit chose to let him have his moment in a small album with like six songs in total? even his outfits are lacking. now i hate to be the grumpy stan that complains about little stupid unimportant things, but i just wanted to mention how weird it seems to me that in an era in which everyone is stunningly amazing, RM is like... okay.
